## Usage\par
\par
```tsx showLineNumbers\par
import \{ Calendar \} from "@/components/ui/calendar"\par
```\par
\par
```tsx showLineNumbers\par
const [date, setDate] = React.useState<Date | undefined>(new Date())\par
\par
return (\par
  <Calendar\par
    mode="single"\par
    selected=\{date\}\par
    onSelect=\{setDate\}\par
    className="rounded-lg border"\par
  />\par
)\par
```\par
\par
See the [React DayPicker](https://react-day-picker.js.org) documentation for more information.\par
\par
## About\par
\par
The `Calendar` component is built on top of [React DayPicker](https://react-day-picker.js.org).\par
\par
## Date Picker\par
\par
You can use the `<Calendar>` component to build a date picker. See the [Date Picker](/docs/components/radix/date-picker) page for more information.\par
\par
## Persian / Hijri / Jalali Calendar\par
\par
To use the Persian calendar, edit `components/ui/calendar.tsx` and replace `react-day-picker` with `react-day-picker/persian`.\par
\par
```diff\par
- import \{ DayPicker \} from "react-day-picker"\par
+ import \{ DayPicker \} from "react-day-picker/persian"\par
```\par
\par
<ComponentPreview\par
  styleName="radix-nova"\par
  name="calendar-hijri"\par
  title="Persian / Hijri / Jalali Calendar"\par
  description="A Persian calendar."\par
  previewClassName="h-[400px]"\par
/>\par
\par
## Selected Date (With TimeZone)\par
\par
The Calendar component accepts a `timeZone` prop to ensure dates are displayed and selected in the user's local timezone.\par
\par
```tsx showLineNumbers\par
export function CalendarWithTimezone() \{\par
  const [date, setDate] = React.useState<Date | undefined>(undefined)\par
  const [timeZone, setTimeZone] = React.useState<string | undefined>(undefined)\par
\par
  React.useEffect(() => \{\par
    setTimeZone(Intl.DateTimeFormat().resolvedOptions().timeZone)\par
  \}, [])\par
\par
  return (\par
    <Calendar\par
      mode="single"\par
      selected=\{date\}\par
      onSelect=\{setDate\}\par
      timeZone=\{timeZone\}\par
    />\par
  )\par
\}\par
```\par
\par
**Note:** If you notice a selected date offset (for example, selecting the 20th highlights the 19th), make sure the `timeZone` prop is set to the user's local timezone.\par
\par
**Why client-side?** The timezone is detected using `Intl.DateTimeFormat().resolvedOptions().timeZone` inside a `useEffect` to ensure compatibility with server-side rendering. Detecting the timezone during render would cause hydration mismatches, as the server and client may be in different timezones.\par
