## Changelog\par
\par
### RTL Support\par
\par
If you're upgrading from a previous version of the `Calendar` component, you'll need to apply the following updates to add locale support:\par
\par
<Steps>\par
\par
<Step>Import the `Locale` type.</Step>\par
\par
Add `Locale` to your imports from `react-day-picker`:\par
\par
```diff\par
  import \{\par
    DayPicker,\par
    getDefaultClassNames,\par
    type DayButton,\par
+   type Locale,\par
  \} from "react-day-picker"\par
```\par
\par
<Step>Add `locale` prop to the Calendar component.</Step>\par
\par
Add the `locale` prop to the component's props:\par
\par
```diff\par
  function Calendar(\{\par
    className,\par
    classNames,\par
    showOutsideDays = true,\par
    captionLayout = "label",\par
    buttonVariant = "ghost",\par
+   locale,\par
    formatters,\par
    components,\par
    ...props\par
  \}: React.ComponentProps<typeof DayPicker> & \{\par
    buttonVariant?: React.ComponentProps<typeof Button>["variant"]\par
  \}) \{\par
```\par
\par
<Step>Pass `locale` to DayPicker.</Step>\par
\par
Pass the `locale` prop to the `DayPicker` component:\par
\par
```diff\par
    <DayPicker\par
      showOutsideDays=\{showOutsideDays\}\par
      className=\{cn(...)\}\par
      captionLayout=\{captionLayout\}\par
+     locale=\{locale\}\par
      formatters=\{\{\par
        formatMonthDropdown: (date) =>\par
-         date.toLocaleString("default", \{ month: "short" \}),\par
+         date.toLocaleString(locale?.code, \{ month: "short" \}),\par
        ...formatters,\par
      \}\}\par
```\par
\par
<Step>Update CalendarDayButton to accept locale.</Step>\par
\par
Update the `CalendarDayButton` component signature and pass `locale`:\par
\par
```diff\par
  function CalendarDayButton(\{\par
    className,\par
    day,\par
    modifiers,\par
+   locale,\par
    ...props\par
- \}: React.ComponentProps<typeof DayButton>) \{\par
+ \}: React.ComponentProps<typeof DayButton> & \{ locale?: Partial<Locale> \}) \{\par
```\par
\par
<Step>Update date formatting in CalendarDayButton.</Step>\par
\par
Use `locale?.code` in the date formatting:\par
\par
```diff\par
    <Button\par
      variant="ghost"\par
      size="icon"\par
-     data-day=\{day.date.toLocaleDateString()\}\par
+     data-day=\{day.date.toLocaleDateString(locale?.code)\}\par
      ...\par
    />\par
```\par
\par
<Step>Pass locale to DayButton component.</Step>\par
\par
Update the `DayButton` component usage to pass the `locale` prop:\par
\par
```diff\par
      components=\{\{\par
        ...\par
-       DayButton: CalendarDayButton,\par
+       DayButton: (\{ ...props \}) => (\par
+         <CalendarDayButton locale=\{locale\} \{...props\} />\par
+       ),\par
        ...\par
      \}\}\par
```\par
\par
<Step>Update RTL-aware CSS classes.</Step>\par
\par
Replace directional classes with logical properties for better RTL support:\par
\par
```diff\par
  // In the day classNames:\par
- [&:last-child[data-selected=true]_button]:rounded-r-(--cell-radius)\par
+ [&:last-child[data-selected=true]_button]:rounded-e-(--cell-radius)\par
- [&:nth-child(2)[data-selected=true]_button]:rounded-l-(--cell-radius)\par
+ [&:nth-child(2)[data-selected=true]_button]:rounded-s-(--cell-radius)\par
- [&:first-child[data-selected=true]_button]:rounded-l-(--cell-radius)\par
+ [&:first-child[data-selected=true]_button]:rounded-s-(--cell-radius)\par
\par
  // In range_start classNames:\par
- rounded-l-(--cell-radius) ... after:right-0\par
+ rounded-s-(--cell-radius) ... after:end-0\par
\par
  // In range_end classNames:\par
- rounded-r-(--cell-radius) ... after:left-0\par
+ rounded-e-(--cell-radius) ... after:start-0\par
\par
  // In CalendarDayButton className:\par
- data-[range-end=true]:rounded-r-(--cell-radius)\par
+ data-[range-end=true]:rounded-e-(--cell-radius)\par
- data-[range-start=true]:rounded-l-(--cell-radius)\par
+ data-[range-start=true]:rounded-s-(--cell-radius)\par
```\par
\par
</Steps>\par
\par
After applying these changes, you can use the `locale` prop to provide locale-specific formatting:\par
\par
```tsx\par
import \{ enUS \} from "react-day-picker/locale"\par
\par
;<Calendar mode="single" selected=\{date\} onSelect=\{setDate\} locale=\{enUS\} />\par
```\par
